Restrictions

In many arenas of life, Ive found constraints and restrictions to inspire creativity. They help to narrow our focus and find workarounds. These are the vague restrictions Ive put on myself for deckbuilding in EDH:

Sylvan Tutor

Mana comes from lands

I doubt this will ever change, but my vote for the EDH banlist is Sol Ring. In my view, its one of the 20 most powerful cards ever printed and yet is included in almost every deck. Boggles my mind to this day that we allow such unbalanced starts. I may build a cEDH deck at some point, but at the moment Im avoiding all mana artifacts and elf style creatures.

This isnt to say that Im playing fair - most of the lists are combo oriented ramp decks - but I get no pleasure from tapping a signet or filling the board with creatures. This dramatically reduces my card

Tutors arent exiciting

My first drafts of the Through the Trees (Azusa - Seasons Combo) back in 2014 had Worldly/Sylvan Tutor and Green Suns Zenith.

I really do enjoy playing lands off the top of my deck, but part of the fun

Big creatures are lame

Tokens are tedious

My turns are already pretty long, I dont need to be doing scute swarm math. My take on creatures in competative magic was principally to kill them or ignore them. Going wide has never really been my idea of fun. Perhaps Ill get bored and build a deck with these guys some day:

Scute swarm Springheart nantuko Greensleeves

Combos are slow and convoluted

Lands are for ladies

For whatever reason most of the land themed characters are female. Not sure why this is but I am just going to roll with it. Sorry bois:

Brstly Bill Greensleeves

I might make an exception for Reki, History of Kamigawa

No ugly

There are several cards that would certainly slot into these decks but theyre so ugly that I cant bear to be seen with them. See the print selections below.

Tato Farmer Shigeki, Jukai Visionary

Aesthetics

As a child, I had some sense of aesthetics when it came to cards but it wasnt very well developed. Now, its one of the main reasons I play EDH and build the decks that I do. Its more fun to perfect
